 News |newspaper=The Standard |location=London |date=17 August 1863 |issue=12173 |page=8 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==15 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=15 August 1863 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Bee'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was holed by a [[groyne]] and sank at [[Eastbourne]], [[Sussex]]. She was on a voyage from [[Hartlepool]], [[County Durham]] to Eastbourne. Following temporary repairs, she was taken in to [[Newhaven, Sussex]] on 17 August.<ref name=NC210863>{{Cite news |title=Marine Intelligence |newspaper=Newcastle Courant |location=Newcastle upon Tyne |date=17 August 1863 |issue=9843 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Her Majesty'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The [[steamship]] struck a rock off [[Bembridge]], [[Isle of Wight]]. Her passengers were taken off by [[pilot boat]]s before she sank. She was on a round the island voyage from [[Ryde]].<ref name=S170863>{{Cite news |title=Wreck of a Passenger Steamer off the Isle of Wight |newspaper=The Standard |location=London |date=17 August 1863 |issue=12173 |page=2 }}</ref> She was refloated on 18 August and towed in to [[Portsmouth]], [[Hampshire]] by the [[tugboat|tug]] ''Echo'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|government}}) and the steamship ''Prince Consort'' ({{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}).<ref name=S190863>{{Cite news |title=Naval and Military Intelligence |newspaper=The Standard |location=London |date=19 August 1863 |issue=12175 |page=3 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Lady Louisa'' \n|flag={{flagcountry|UKGBI|civil}}\n|desc=The ship was driven ashore between the [[Hurst Spit]] and [[Lymington]], [[Hampshire]]. She was on a voyage from [[Waterford]] to [[Southampton]], Hampshire. She was refloated and completed her voyage.<ref name=S190863a/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==16 August==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=16 August 1863 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Bellona'' \n|flag={{flagicon|UKGBI}} [[British North 